<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Mission Statement</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="image57.gif" WIDTH="306" HEIGHT="72" ALIGN=bottom 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<IMG SRC="image104.gif" WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"><IMG SRC="image114.gif" WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></CENTER>
<P>The <STRONG>Texas Association of Student Councils</STRONG> is a non profit
organization officially sponsored by the <A HREF="mainmenu.htm">Texas Association
of Secondary School Principals.</A> Its goals as defined by the <A HREF="Constit.htm">TASC
constitution </A>are to &quot;instill American ideals, to develop citizenship
and to encourage student councils in the secondary schools&quot; of the
state.<BR>
<BR>
Over 1,400 high schools and junior high or middle schools have organized
Student Councils that participate in TASC activities. (Click here for <A HREF="student.htm">What
is a Student Council?</A>) By voluntarily joining together to support one
another through the state association, these schools offer themselves a
multitude of services. The Association's 60 year history is a tribute to
sponsors and students of past member schools who provided such a strong
heritage of service and support. The work of TASC is accomplished not just
through the state office in Austin, but through the work of thousands of
youth and adults in the schools of the state. 
<H4>TASC NEWSLETTER StuCo Review</H4>
Published 5 times each school year, the newletter provides members with
current information about what the association offers. It includes registration
information for all TASC activities listed above, plus news from TASC Districts
and member schools. <A HREF="http://www.intpub.com/tassp/stuco.htm">To Search
previous issues click here.</A> 
<H4>TASC SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM</H4>
Several Outstanding senior students are recognized each year with $500 scholarships
in honor of their achievements and contributions to Student Council. <A HREF="scholar.htm">Click
for more details.</A> 
<H4>RECOGNITION PROGRAMS FOR LOCAL COUNCILS</H4>
TASC recognizes hundreds of high schools and middle schools in Texas each
year for their work in Health and Safety, Energy and the Environment, SMILE,
Pride and Patriotism, and for overall Outstanding Student Council Programs.
For more information and a copy of the report forms, <A HREF="tascrep.htm">click
here.</A> 
<H4>LEADERSHIP COURSE CURRICULUM</H4>
TASC is committed to providing leadership opportunities and training for
as many students as possible. With the summer workshops, district conferences,
state conferences and other &quot;meeting&quot; formats, TASC reaches in
excess of 10,000 students each year. To broaden and strengthen the opportunities
available to Texas students, the Association, with the support of TASSP,
has arranged for an experimental course curriculum to be available to Texas
High Schools during 1996 - 97. For additional information, <A HREF="mailto:%20ebull@tassp.org">contact
the TASC office</A><A HREF="mailto:bgreen@tassp.org">.</A> 
<H4>DISTRICT ORGANIZATION</H4>
The state is divided geographically into <A HREF="tascmap.htm">19 TASC Districts</A>.
Each district is governed by a District Executive Committee and provides
services to its member schools. Districts conduct elections for District
offices, screen and report District schools to be recognized in TASC Recognition
programs, and offer a structure of support for newly organized councils,
new Student Council advisors, and Principals. 
<H4>TASC INSIGNIA</H4>
Attractive lapel pins, patches, guards depicting the TASC Star Insignia
are available from <A HREF="mailto:jostens@info.net">Josten's.</A> <BR>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="tascmis.html">About TASC </A>/ <A HREF="tasceven.htm">Upcoming
Events</A> / <A HREF="tascrep.htm">Project Report Forms</A> / <BR>
<A HREF="http://aus.computize.com/bulletin/tasc/default.html">On-line Focus
Sessions</A> / <A HREF="tasclinks.htm">Links</A> / <A HREF="Project.htm">Project
List </A>/ <A HREF="mainmenu.htm">TASSP</A> / <A HREF="tasc.htm">Home</A></CENTER>
</BODY>
