<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>TAFE Background Info</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="image115.gif" WIDTH="319" HEIGHT="82" ALIGN=bottom
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<A HREF="tafemis.html"><IMG SRC="image88.gif" WIDTH="199" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN=
bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="0"></A></CENTER>
<H3>Background</H3>
The Texas Association of Future Educators (TAFE) was started in 1984 and
is sponsored by the Texas Association of Secondary School Principals (TASSP).
In 1995-96 there are about 200 member schools, representing all parts of
the state. Headquarters are located in Austin. 
<H3>Purposes</H3>
<UL>The organization was founded in order to: 
<LI>Recruit qualified youth to become teachers to eliminate shortages within
the profession. 
<LI>Provide students with valuable experiences in high school that will
keep them committed to becoming teachers throughout their college career.
<LI>Counsel and provide information to students to change and enhance the
image of the teaching profession. 
<LI>Create a condition in our state where the very best and brightest students
choose to become educators. 
</UL>
<H3>Membership</H3>
Open to all high school, middle school and junior high school students.
Junior and middle school participation is limited to the local and district
levels. 
<H3>Sponsorship</H3>
Any teacher with a sincere interest in working with students and enthusiasm
for the teaching profession is welcome as a sponsor. TAFE is not affiliated
with any one teacher organization. 
<H3>Dues</H3>
$35 per year per school. 
<H3>State Organization</H3>
TAFE is governed by a policy-making <A HREF="../../TASSP%20docs/tafe.htm/tafe">Board
of Directors</A> which consists of the following people: 
<OL>
<LI>The Executive Director of TAFE/TASSP 
<LI>One student and the head sponsor of each of four officer schools 
<LI>Three elected TAFE sponsors 
<LI>Three members of the TASSP Board of Directors 
<LI>The sponsor of the immediate past president school 
</OL>
The state office provides support and information for the local organization,
publishes four <A HREF="../../TASSP%20docs/tafe.htm/tafe">newsletters</A>
a year, and sponsors the following <A HREF="../../TASSP%20docs/tafe.htm/tafe">statewide
conferences and workshops:</A> 
<UL>
<LI>Sponsors' Workshop - one-day workshop held in September 
<LI>Annual Conference - two-day conference held in early Spring 
<LI>Summer Workshop - a week-long workshop held in June 
<LI>Two $1000 <A HREF="../../TASSP%20docs/tafe.htm/speech">scholarships</A>
are awarded at the Annual Conference to the winners of the TAFE Outstanding
Speech Contest. 
</UL>
<H3>District</H3>
<A HREF="tafemap.htm">The state is divided into 20 districts.</A> Each district
is encouraged to hold a district convention. 
<H3>Local</H3>
Each school chapter operates independently according to its constitution
and school district rules and regulations. For a well-rounded program, we
encourage the following activities: 
<UL>
<LI>Teaching or Tutoring Experiences 
<LI>Recreation 
<LI>Appreciation Activities for Teachers and Staff 
<LI>Fund Raising 
<LI>Leadership Training 
<LI>Education and Growth in the Profession 
<LI>Service Projects at School and in the Community 
</UL>
For more information on TAFE projects see <A HREF="tafeproj.htm">Top Ten
Projects. </A><BR>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="tafemis.html">About TAFE </A>/ <A HREF="tafeproj.htm">Project
List</A> / <A HREF="http://aus.computize.com/bulletin/tafe/default.html">On-line
Focus Sessions</A> <BR>
<A HREF="tafe.htm">Home</A> / <A HREF="mainmenu.htm">TASSP</A> </CENTER>
</BODY>
</HTML>
