<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Texas Study Of Secondary Education</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="/Gil%27s%20Drive/Desktop%20Folder/tsse%20header%20%26%20gif/brn_krft.gif">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="header.gif" WIDTH="432" HEIGHT="126" ALIGN=bottom 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<BR>
</CENTER>
<BR>
The <I>Texas Study of Secondary Education</I> is the association's professional
journal. Members receive this publication twice a year, in the spring and
in the fall. Each issue focuses on one or more broad topics of interest
to secondary school administrators. Austhors include both state and nationally
recognized experts. Addtiionally in the <I>Texas Study</I> you will read
articles on current topics as well as humorous anecdotes contributed by
members. <BR>
<BR>
To contribute an article or an anecdote or to subscribe to the Texas Study
if you are a non-member, contact TASSP at: (512) 443-2100 or e-mail the
managing editor <A HREF="mailto:drinken@tassp.org">Dawn Rinken.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</A>The following issues have been updated for the TASSP web site, in text
format.<BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="sp1996.htm">Spring 1996 (Vol V. No.2)</A><BR>
Back to <A HREF="public3.htm">Publications</A>
