<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Member Classifications</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="image51.gif" WIDTH="392" HEIGHT="54" ALIGN=bottom 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<STRONG>MEMBERSHIP CLASSIFICATIONS 1996-97</STRONG></CENTER>
<P>Topic: TASSP Member Classifications<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="ACT"><STRONG>ACTIVE MEMBERSHIPS:</STRONG></A><STRONG> Limited to
individuals who are actively engaged in secondary school administration.<BR>
<BR>
TASSP State Membership: ($87)</STRONG> Includes subscriptions to TASSP News
Highlights, Texas Study of Secondary Education, and special publications;
state conferences and workshops; $5,000 Accidental Death & Dismemberment
insurance policy; job placement service; and answers to individual inquiries
on administrative and legal questions. In addition each active member selects
membership in one of five divisions/roundtables that focus on more specific
aspects of secondary education:<BR>
<BR>
<I>Division of High School Education:</I> Concerned with the structure and
function of high school (9-12) and applying TASSP objectives to that setting.<BR>
<I>Division of Middle Level Education:</I> Concerned with the structure
and function of the middle school (5-9), and applying TASSP objectives to
that setting.<BR>
<I>Division of Secondary Curriculum & Instruction:</I> Concerned with curriculum
and instructional issues at all levels of secondary education; primarily
of interest to central office and campus level personnel with responsibilities
limited to these areas.<BR>
<I>Assistant Principals Roundtable:</I> Concerned with meeting the needs
of assistant principals, associate principals, deans, and others who may
or may not be interested in advancing to the principalship.<BR>
<I>Small Schools Roundtable:</I> Concerned with meeting the needs of principals
from smaller high schools, Jr. High - High School combinations, or K-12
schools. <BR>
<BR>
<A NAME = "INS"><STRONG>TASSP Liability Insurance: ($40)</STRONG> </A><I>Available
only with paid TASSP active membership.</I> Includes $1,000,000 liability
insurance, reimbursement of attorney fees, and punitive insurance damages
as described in the master policy. Not available after January 31 of the
current school year.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME = "NIND"><STRONG>NASSP Individual Membership: ($165)</STRONG> </A><I>(Please
note that National membership does not include TASSP State membership.)</I>
Subscriptions to NASSP Bulletin, Legal Update, Newsleader and special publications;
NASSP conventions and Frontline Conferences; $400,000 NASSP liability policy.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME = "NINS"><STRONG>NASSP Institutional Membership: ($215)</STRONG>
</A>NASSP services as listed for NASSP Individual Membership. Covers one
named member and includes an extra set of all NASSP publications for school
professional library.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>RETIRED MEMBERSHIPS: Available to individuals who were active or
associate members before they retired.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME = "RET">TASSP Retired Membership: ($10)</STRONG> </A>Includes all
TASSP services except insurance.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>NASSP Retired Membership: </STRONG>Open to former NASSP members
who retired after at least 10 years of membership. Choose one of two plans:<BR>
<BR>
<I>Full Service: </I><STRONG>($55)</STRONG> Provides the same services as
for an NASSP Individual membership.<BR>
<I>Basic Service: </I><STRONG>($25)</STRONG> Designed for those not wanting
to continue to receive all the publications. Includes the Newsleader.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME = "ASS"><STRONG>ASSOCIATE MEMBERSHIPS:</A>Available to persons in
non-administrative positions or other persons interested and involved in
secondary education.<BR>
<BR>
TASSP Associate: ($40)</STRONG> Includes all TASSP services except insurance.<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME = "PROF"><STRONG>PROFESSORS/FULL-TIME GRADUATE STUDENTS:</A> Reduced
state and national memberships are available for qualifying professors of
educational administration and full-time graduate students in these departments.
Contact TASSP for details.<BR>
<P><CENTER></STRONG><A HREF="about.htm">About Tassp</A> / <A HREF="news.htm">News
and Announcements</A> / <A HREF="member.htm">Member Services<BR>
</A><A HREF="http://aus.computize.com/bulletin/default.html">Online Discussion</A>
/ <A HREF="relsites.htm">Related Sites</A> / <A HREF="regact.htm">Regional
Activities<BR>
<BR>
