<H2>CANYON HIGH SCHOOL</H2>
BOX 1200, Canyon, TX  79015

<H3>NAME OF PROJECT:  G.I.N. (Get Involved Now) PARTY</H3>

<H3>PURPOSE:</H3>  To develop a better involvement in school activities for new students and sophomores.  To develop better school spirit within the new students and sophomore class.  To develop a better attitude of the new students and sophomores.  To develop new friendships and relationships with the student body.

<H3>DESCRIPTION:</H3>  At the beginning of the school year, the new students and sophomores were invited to an informal party.  Following a welcome given by the principal, everyone participated in leadership games such as mixers and team activities, sang songs, learned of upcoming projects, learned the school song, and ate watermelon.  Approximately 100 new students and sophomores attended.  The new students were then given an activity pass enabling them to attend any school activity free of charge for three weeks.

<p>Through the G.I.N. Party, students were given the opportunity to get involved and build new friendships.  In return, this project enabled the students to become more active, thus developing relationships and friendships which would last throughout the rest of everyones high school years.  The party also gave the new students and sophomores the opportunity to meet some members of the Student Council so they knew someone to ask for help or information.
