<H2>CORSICANA HIGH SCHOOL,W. HWY. 22, CORSICANA, TEXAS  75110</H2>

<H3>NAME OF PROJECT:  Student Leadership Day</H3>

<H3>PURPOSE OF PROJECT</H3><OL>
	<LI>To enable students to learn by experience about a particular career
	<LI>To make the community aware of potential career talent as represented by 	CHS juniors and seniors
	<LI>To enable local business people to see and become aware of the high school 	facilities
	<LI>To work with the Corsicana Chamber of Commerce
</OL>
<H2>BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF PROJECT</H2>
<p>The CHS Student Council came up with a project that would allow CHS students to spend a school day on a particular job to learn pros and cons of the job.  The Council went to the Chamber of Commerce with the project.

<p>Student Leadership Day involves CHS students and faculty, the local Chamber of Commerce, and many local business people in a very worthwhile project.  The project is open to all CHS juniors and seniors.

<p>Students are asked to sign a sheet and tell what career field they would like to learn more about.  They are told to put a particular business they would like to be placed with if they have a preference.

<p>Once the sign-up sheets are in, the Student Council committee goes to the Chamber of Commerce, and together they place each student with a particular business or job the student has requested.

<p>The students are then told where they will spend Student Leadership Day.  On that day, the business people come to the high school for coffee and donuts and a tour of the school.  After the tour, the business people meet with the students, and from there they go to the business or job.

<p>The business people are asked to tell the students about all facets of that career; education required, pay, benefits, etc.  The business people provide lunch for the students, and the students must stay until the business closes.

<p>Thank you letters are sent to each business, merchant, etc., who has taken a part in Student Leadership Day.

<H3>DESCRIPTION OF INVOLVEMENT AND RESPONSES</H3>
<p>With a junior and senior class of approximately five hundred, 178 students participated in the project this year.

<p>Local business people in the community were most willing to be a part of the project.  By having the business people meet at the high school that morning, the Student Council was able to get many community members to visit the school.

<p>While the project was for juniors and seniors, freshmen and sophomore Student Council members showed the business people around the school.

<p>The Chamber of Commerce was very pleased with the results of the project.  The High School principal said it was an outstanding learning experience for all involved.
</DOC>
