<title>REACH OUT AND TOUCH</title>

<h2>DEERPARK MIDDLE SCHOOL, ROUND ROCK MIDDLE SCHOOL AND
SPRING WOODS MIDDLE SCHOOL, HOUSTON</h2>

<p>This project involved two student councils.  The purposes were 1) To provide communication, motivation, and bonding between councils; 2) to provide the councils with new activities for the school year; and 3) to bring new campus improvement ideas to each campus.

<p>A brief description of the various activities used to accomplish these purposes follow:

<h3>PEN PALS:</h3>
<p>Council members from each school wrote letters to each other sharing information about themselves and their schools.  Class teams were formed at both schools and they corresponded as well.

<h3>MINUTES:</h3>
<p>Throughout the school year, councils exchanged minutes from each of their student council meetings to get an idea of what each other was doing for their school and community.

<h3>TELEPHONE:</h3>
<p>Councils used Video Tel from Southwestern Bell to keep in touch with each other face to face.

<h3>VIDEO and SLIDE SHOW:</h3>
<p>The student body form each school participated in preparing a video and slide show of their schools.  The shows were exchanged and copies remained at their respective schools to share with incoming students.

<h3>SERVICE PROJECT:</h3>
<p>Council members from each of the schools met halfway between Round Rock and Houston and cleaned up a highway rest area.

<h3>STATE and DISTRICT CONVENTIONS:</h3>
<p>Together, the student councils planned and presented a discussion group on this project at state and district conventions.

<h3>SCHOOL VISITS:</h3>
<p>Twelve members of the councils visited each other's schools and reported their findings to their Campus Improvement Teams.

<p>This project allowed two councils to meet and get to know each other and provided a common bond of leadership and friendship.


</DOC>
