<heading>public relations</heading>
<H2>GRAPEVINE HIGH SCHOOL</H2>

<H3>NAME OF PROJECT:  Mustang Forum</H3>

<H3>PURPOSE:</H3>  To open a line of communication among students, teachers, administrators and the community.

<H3>OBJECTIVES:</H3><OL>
	<LI>Organize a group atmosphere where students, faculty, administration, and 	community members feel comfortable expressing ideas and concerns about any 	topic.
	<LI>Organize sign-ups for this weekly event.
	<LI>Insure that this event runs smoothly and does not turn into a gripe 	session/free-for-all.
	<LI>Insure immediate feedback from administration.

<H3>DESCRIPTION:</H3>
<P>Mustang Forum meets in the GHS lecture hall every Thursday alternating between A&B lunches.  Everyone is welcomed to attend as part of the audience or to present a topic.  Students, community members, teachers, and administrators call or sign up to present topics to the forum two days in advance.  The student council president introduces each speaker and acts as moderator when audience asks questions or has comments.  There are administrators present at each Mustang Forum to give immediate feedback and to list concerns to present at the district principals' meeting  Through Mustang Forum, we have recalled one handbook dress code rule, set up an off-campus lunch pass reward system for with perfect attendance, and set up a committee to review the procedure and effectiveness of our morning announcements.  The student body has learned a great deal about state and local district rules concerning education and the decision making process one must go through to institute a change in those rules.

<H3>INVOLVEMENT:</H3>
<P>Mustang Forum is organized by the GHS student council.  We are in charge of sign-ups, presenting speakers, and moderating discussions.  Stuco members sign up students and staff members during lunch periods two days prior to the Thursday forum date.  We also man our stuco phone for community members who may be interested in attending or presenting at the forum.  

<p>The student body, including all clubs and organizations, is encouraged to attend Mustang Forum and to sign up to present a topic of concern.  The faculty is also encouraged to attend or present at the forum.  The Grapevine-Colleyville ISD superintendent calls each week to inquire about topics we will be presenting at Mustang Forum and attends when his schedule allows.  If a scheduled topic pertains to a club or organization within the school, that group is notified so that they can be included in the discussion.  The community was informed through the area newspapers about Mustang Forum earlier in the school year.  So far, one school board candidate and a member of the Grapevine Citizens Advisory Committee have addressed Mustang Forum about community concerns.

</DOC>
