<H2>GILLETT MIDDLE SCHOOL,KINGSVILLE</H2>

<H3>OBJECTIVE:<H3>
<p>To recognize students and school personnel for special accomplishments.
To promote technology in the area of communication at GMS.

<p>The Gillett Student Council has formed a broadcasting news network called Bobcat Network News Show (BNN).  GMS as adopted by CENCOM Cable TV.  Student council members form the production company but there is open enrollment for the jobs of reporters.  BNN has 30 student council members and 20 other students who serve as reporters.  Each teacher has a reporter assigned to him or her, and all extra-curricular organizations have a reporter assigned to them as well.

<p>The show features students and teachers and covers academic and extra-curricular activities.  The show has a segment called "Connie's Corner."  Connie has interviewed the school board president, superintendent, county sheriff, and DARE officer.  She has also interviewed a panel of math teachers and the 4-H ribbon winners.

<p>Another segment is called Michael's Tips where Michael gives tips on how to solve math problems, how to diagram sentences, and even tips on how to improve your tennis game.  There is also a segment where the GMS president makes student council announcements and gives health and safety information.

<P>BNN also films programs, special lessons requested by the teachers, and all guests on our campus.  Our script writer combines the reports and prepares the scripts.  We have two girls who write cue cards.  We handle all the editing at CENCOM Cable TV but filming is done at Gillett Middle School twice a month.

<P>The principal participates by making announcements and addressing students, parents and the community.  Parents watch the program to see what their children are doing in school and for reports on future events.  The show airs every two weeks on Thursday at 6:30 p.m.

<H3>Evaluation:</H3>
<p>The BNN project has been an excellent source of student and teacher recognition.  It has taught students many communication skills such as writing reports, use of a camera, editing, and use of sound equipment.  The technology that CENCOM has exposed our students to is immeasurable for this age group.  The self-esteem they have developed by seeing themselves on TV is remarkable.

<H3>Cost:</H3>
<p>We started with a school camera but after the school board became interested in our project, a camera was purchased for us.  The expenses incurred for BNN were for VCR tapes, markers, posters, and computer paper.



</DOC>
