<H2>JOHN JAY HIGH SCHOOLSAN ANTONIO</H2>

<H3>NAME OF PROJECT:  Class Spirit Competition</H3>

<H3>PURPOSE AND OBJECTIVES:</H3>  To develop competition between the classes to promote class spirit; to improve the attitude of the students; to stress the importance of cleanliness of the school; to provide support for our athletes

<H3>DESCRIPTION:</H3>
<p>The Student Council is sponsoring a spirit competition, which is a competition between the freshmen, sophomore, junior, and senior classes.  This competition is designed to continue throughout the entire school year.

<H3>Criteria for points:</H3>
<p>The four classes receive points for having the most members of their class in attendance to home varsity sports, cleaning the halls where their lockers are located, cleaning a designated part of the campus, maintaining an orderly attitude during their class meetings and carrying out any extra-ordinary projects to promote spirit.  Points were awarded in a four, three, two, one fashion for each event.  First place receiving four points, second place receiving three points, etc.

<p>All judging was done by council members and various members of the faculty and administration.
<p>A running total of points is posted on the Student Council bulletin board.  The class with the most point at the end of the school year will receive a large spirit trophy.  This is the first your of the competition and will continue on throughout the years.

<H3>INVOLVEMENT:</H3>
<p>The students actively participate in the various competitions with support for their individual class.  Students Council is involved in that it is in charge of advertising and supporting the various projects.  Student Council members counted people from each class at the home varsity sports events besides football.  The cheerleaders counted at the football games because of the enormous number of students.  The administration judged most competitions to insure honesty and no partiality.  The community was involved in that they noticed an increase in numbers and spirit at the games and an overall change in attitude of the students.  The campus is also much cleaner because of the students' efforts.  

<H3>EVALUATION:</H3>
<p>This project is proving to be a big success.  Students' attitudes have improved greatly due to the fact that halls are cleaner, attendance at games has improved and assemblies are conducted in a decent manner.

</DOC>
