<H2>DUMAS JUNIOR HIGH SCHOOL</H2>

<H3>NAME OF PROJECT:  Hello Week</H3>

<H3>PURPOSE and OBJECTIVE:</H3>
<p>To promote a better relationship for students, faculty, and parents.  To create a community awareness that it takes all of us working together for our kids to make them feel important.  Ideally, to reduce the drop-out rate by making school an atmosphere of learning and fun--giving the at-risk students some way to get involved.

<H3>DESCRIPTION:</H3>
<p>This event was held one evening in early September at our football stadium.  It was the culmination of HELLO week.  Each activity involved teachers, administrators, parents, and students.  The only activity that cost money was the dunking board.  We had a sound system to announce all activities and prize giveaways.  We had volleyball nets set up and stations for each of the events.  Local merchants donated refreshments--watermelons and kool-aid.  They also donated the prizes: free pizzas, hamburgers, meals, ice cream, cokes, etc.

<p>The event was advertised in the local newspaper, on the radio station, and on the community cable channel.  We also sent home flyers (in Spanish) with our students who live in Cactus, and provided a bus to transport them the 15 miles into town and back home.  We had a fantastic turn-out--over 800 students, nearly all the junior high staff, and an abundance of parents and people from the community.

<H3>INVOLVEMENT:</H3>
<p>Student council members were responsible for demonstrating some of the events, helping with the refreshments, clean-up, and keeping everyone active and enthusiastic.

<P>We asked students who were not involved with the student council to help set up, distribute flyer, demonstrate activities, and get their friends and parents to participate.

<p>Other groups in our school, CVAE and boys' athletics, helped set up the volleyball nets and the dunking booth, etc..  Nearly every one of the faculty members was present.  They helped by manning stations and helping with the clean-up.  Parents and other community members helped by manning the stations and the refreshment tables, by taking pictures, and by participating in the events and the clean-up.

<H3>ACTIVITIES:</H3><UL>

<LI>7:00			Bat Race
<LI>7:20			Pantyhose Race
<LI>7:40			2-legged Race with water balloons
<LI>8:00			Tricycle Race
<LI>8:20			Inner tube Race
<LI>8:40			Necking with Oranges
<LI>9:00			Lifesavers
</UL>
</DOC>
