<HTML>"Notes from the TASSP Board of Directors' Meeting -- January 24, 1996"<p><p>
<p><p>
from <strong>TASSP News Highlights</strong>; March 1996; Vol. 35, No. 4; p. 3p><p>
<p><p>
The TASSP Directors met at the Town Lake Holiday Inn in Austin on January 24, 1996. Thirty-nine of forty-two Board members were present. The following actions were taken by the Board:<p>
1. Reviewed and approved a tentative agenda for the Summer Workshop.<p>
2. Received the evaluation summary and preliminary financial statement on the National Conference of Texas.<p>
3. Approved the report and recommendations of the TASSP Technology Committee (see accompanying story on p. 12-13).<p>
4. Reviewed and approved the 1994-95 TASSP Audit.<p>
5. Heard an extensive review of the 1995-96 Budget.<p>
6. Approved the awarding of $500 unrestricted scholarships to the twenty regional academic excellence winners.<p>
7. Approved the recommendation of the Principals Image Committee that Mr. Donald Pinson from John Marshall High School be selected as the Texas Assistant Principal of the Year.<p>
8. Reviewed and approved resource materials for the proposed Constitutional Amendment changing the method of setting membership fees.<p>
9. Approved a joint effort with TEA to develop, distribute and compile data surveying the needs of Texas principals.<p>
10. Approved support for a Regional Instructional Leadership Academy Pilot Project.<p>
11. Various miscellaneous business.<p>
All coordinators and representatives are commended for their attendance and active participation in TASSP business meetings.</html>

