<H1>Collaborating with Genentech</H1>
</CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE>


<FONT SIZE=+3>D</FONT>eveloping alliances that build on the company's strengths has always been one of Genentech's strategies for success. In 1978 the company entered into a landmark biotech collaboration when Genentech licensed rights to recombinant human insulin to Eli Lilly and Company.<P>
 

The corporate mission -- to discover, develop, manufacture and market human pharmaceuticals for significant unmet medical needs -- is echoed in Genentech's commitment and efforts to enter into strategic alliances that facilitate Genentech's and our partners' efforts to develop and commercialize novel pharmaceutical products that address significant unmet medical needs.<P>
