<DOCHDR>
http://outcast.gene.com:80/Company/achievement.html 192.216.245.8 19970124065739 text/html 3035
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
Date: Fri, 24 Jan 1997 06:57:36 GMT
Server: NCSA/1.4.1
Content-type: text/html
Last-modified: Fri, 12 Apr 1996 19:15:22 GMT
Content-length: 2859
</DOCHDR>
<html><head><TITLE>Scientific Acheivements</TITLE></head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>

<!-- begin-gne-header -->
<a href=/cgi-bin/imagemap/about_gne>
<img border=0 src=about_gne.gif alt=About Genentech ismap></a>
<!-- end-gne-header -->

<H1>Scientific Achievements</H1></CENTER>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<img border=0 align=left hspace=10 vspace=10 src="sci_acheiv.gif">
<FONT SIZE=+3>G</FONT>enentech's most important asset is its science.  The company's research has led to ten -- almost half -- of all biotechnology-based products on the market today.  Genentech is the only biotechnology company to have taken five of its own products from the laboratory to the marketplace.  The other five products stemming from Genentech research are licensed to other companies.
<P>

Genentech scientists are the most prolific in the biotechnology industry, publishing at a rate of about 250 papers per year.  The company is also the leader among biotechnology and pharmaceutical companies for average number of citations per published scientific paper -- a peer-related measure considered to be a good indication of scientific impact.  Genentech holds more than 1,500 patents worldwide, and has more than 1,200 pending.
<P>

Genentech was the first biotechnology company to successfully scale-up protein manufacturing from small quantities used for research to the much larger quantities needed for clinical trials and marketing.  The company continues to be a world leader in the manufacture of biopharmaceuticals, producing up to 50 kilograms of many products yearly for clinical research and the marketplace, through a variety of fermentation and proprietary purification processes.  This amount -- about the weight of a very large dog -- may not seem like much until one considers that these proteins are produced by microscopic organisms and that doses are measured in milligrams, a unit about 1/1000 the weight of a paper clip.
<P>
<img align=right src=frc.gif>
To help ensure continued scientific excellence, Genentech opened the world's largest research facility devoted solely to biotechnology in October, 1992.  A 275,000-square-foot, $85 million facility, the Founders Research Center features specialized laboratories and equipment and three inter-connected buildings overlooking the San Francisco Bay.  It houses more than 400 Genentech scientists and staff members.  The Founders Research Center is dedicated to Robert Swanson and Dr. Herbert Boyer in honor of their pursuit of the promise of biotechnology when they established Genentech more than 17 years ago.  A new $62.5 million Process Science Center opened in 1995 adds to Genentech's state-of-the-science facilities.

</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>

