<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Executive Assistant
Requisition #:    97-0000054

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Provide executive assistance to the Senior Director of Pharmacological Sciences and administrative support for the Pharmacology Review Committee.  Responsibilities include a wide range of diverse and complex administrative duties: establish priorities for appointments/correspondence/issues; schedule meetings and attend when necessary; make travel arrangements; plan both on and off-site meetings; draft/prepare correspondence, reports, agendas and meeting summaries; coordinate/prepare presentation materials.  Work on special projects, as assigned.  In addition, prepare and monitor budget; establish policies/procedures to streamline and direct administrative activities across the organization; and oversee planning for the group's space needs and remodels.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Minimum of 10 years experience as an Assistant with at least three years as an Adminstrative Manager.  Excellent written/oral communication skills; knowledge of scienctific/medical language.  Proficient in computer systems, with working knowledge of the Mac, Word, Persuausion, Excel, and other administrative computer tools.  Ability to work independently and as a team player.  Experience in analyzing and creating effective systems/processes to solve administrative problems.  Position requires considerable judgment, discretion and diplomacy with the demonstrated ability to work with individuals at all levels.  BS in Business Administration preferred.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

