<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Application Analyst/Senior Application Analyst
Requisition #:    97-0000049

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
As a member of a drug development project team, the Applications Analyst helps plan, design, develop, implement, and maintain software for the monitoring, reporting, and analysis of clinical trials.  Develop and execute software to monitor ongoing studies, produce data listing, summary tables and graphics for interim and final analyses.  Create statistical files for biostatistical analysis and integrate data across studies within a project.  Test and document all programs according to department guidelines.  Provide consulting and systems support for applications software.  Help train others in the use of generalized application software.  Assist in the maintenance of applications software by identifying enhancements with the software developer.  Identify areas where new standardized software tools are needed.  Review the CRF design for new clinical studies, data management plans and database specifications for impact on software systems.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS Degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience.  Minimum of 2 years of SAS Programming.  Knowledge of the SAS programming language especially data step programming and the SAS macro language, programming standards and accepted software development techniques.  Skilled in use of graphics software usage, e.g., SAS/Graph, S-Plus, or SAS/IML.  Knowledge and familiarity with data base theory, specifically relational database concepts and SQL.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

