<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Provide support to the Medical Affairs Finance group by preparing confidentiality and fee for service agreements with outside consultants and other vendors.  Take primary responsibility for document handling in the MA Finance area - FedEx, copying, filing and tracking, including participation in the supervision of temporary Administrative Assistants.  Maintain information in a contracts database.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
High School degree required, college degree preferred.  A basic familiarity with contracts is highly preferable.  Must be a highly organized self-starter who is comfortable working in a fast-paced environment with frequent tight deadlines.  Excellent interpersonal and communication skills required.  Must be Macintosh fluent using Excel, Word, and FileMaker Pro.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
