<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Database Administrator
Requisition #:    96-0001019

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The Database Administrator in Operations Drug Safety is responsible for the non-technical administration of the corporate drug safety database.  The corporate drug safety database contains all adverse event reports from spontaneous sources and all adverse events form clinical studies that meet the criteria of regulatory agencies for seriousness.  Responsibilities include quality control, production of specialized queries, import/export of cases, and liaison with internal groups within Medical Affairs. The Database Administrator participate in safety-related educational activities for drug safety staff and other Genentech staff involved in the sharing of information on drug safety. This person is not directly responsible for purely technical administration but will work with Systems Level Administration who maintain the UNIX and ORACLE environments for the database. General administrative duties.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS/BA in Life Sciences.  Experience with drug safety reports for a bio/pharmaceutical company is desired.  Need knowledge of medical terminology.  Demonstrated proficiency with computer databases.  Aptitude to master search tools such as Brio Query or SQL.  Accuracy and attention to detail. Must have excellent interpersonal and organizational skills.  Demonstrated ability to work with professional people of widely varying background.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

