<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Senior Systems Analyst
Requisition #:    96-0000888

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Lead the specification, design, development, implementation and support of database systems and applications required by Medical Affairs for the clinical development process.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Experience developing, implementing and supporting database applications for clinical development in the pharmaceutical or biotechnology industries.  Experience planning and managing systems integration and development projects.  Familiarity with Sun network servers, Apple Macintosh clients, and TCP/IP telecommunications technologies.  Basic familiarity with workflow, imaging, statistical analysis, document management and object-oriented programming.  Bachelors degree in computer science or a related discipline.  A Masters degree is strongly preferred.  Minimum of 3 years commercial experience with database systems design, development, implementation and support in the UNIX environment.  Formal technical training on Informix or Oracle.Training on both systems preferred.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

