<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Application Technical Support Specialist
Requisition #:    97-0000052

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Provides direct technical assistance for a large user base at Genentech.  Skilled at providing end user support in a help desk environment.  Must be able to teach technical and non-technical users how to use supported and locally developed systems; helps to produce end-user documentation and training materials.  Teaches workshops for users.  Broad familiarity with modern information technology, both hardware and software, particularly information technology in use at Genentech.  May design information technology procedures and systems which incorporate computing, data management, and communications for Genentech's business needs.  Will serve as primary contact for the POMS Manufacturing Execution System (MES) and as backup contact for the BPCS Manufacturing Resource Planning (MRP system) and NovaManage Electronic Data Management Systems (EDMS).  Maintains relationship with vendors and communicates and works closely with IR.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS in relevant field or 4 years of applicable experience.   Technical proficiency in user area.  Ability to work as part of a large team and communicate at various levels.  Ability to learn quickly and apply skills to projects.  Ability to juggle multiple projects, project requests and appropriately prioritize.  Windows, NT, Macintosh experience required.  Oracle and C++ preferred.  Team player with the necessary strengths to work effectively in a highly dynamic and demanding project.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
