<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Biochem Technologist
Requisition #:    96-0000623

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Responsible for monitoring, troubleshooting, and optimizing manufacturing operations.  Also responsible for training, document review, and clinical production leadership in Cell Culture Production.  Will investigate, and coordinate manufacturing issues.  Train the CCP staff.  Optimize manufacturing systems and equipment.  Introduce new equipment and technologies.  Review documentation for completeness and correctness.  Resolve documentation issues.  Provide leadership on projects, process improvements, and teams.  Assist in establishing and maintaining CCP facilities at inspection readiness.  Provide technician performance feedback to supervisors.  Participate in continuing education programs.  Facilitate technical interactions between CCP staff and other departments to meet department/company goals and objectives.        
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BA/BS in biological or physical sciences.  Minimum of four years work experience in cGMP biopharmaceutical production.  Strong understanding of large scale cell culture and protein purification.  Successful demonstration of technical expertise, problem solving, training, organizations, and initiative.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
