<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Biochemical Technician
Requisition #:    97-0000004

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Responsible for manufacturing operations in the Cell Culture Production facility, to include media preparation, fermentation, buffer preparation and purification.  Duties include operation of filtration equipment and liquid chromatography equipment, clean, prepare and autoclave glassware and components.  Clean, sterilize, batch and monitor tanks and fermenters.  Follow Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), manufacturing tickets forms, Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP) and safety guidelines.  Operate computers for process control and data entry.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS/BA in life sciences or equivalent.  Good interpersonal and communication skills.  Must be able to work weekends, off-shifts and overtime as required.  Mechanical aptitude, microbiology, or protein purification skills are desirable.  Must be able to lift 30 pounds and work extended periods standing up.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
