<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Contract Manufacturing Specialist
Requisition #:    96-0000989

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The Contract Manufacturing Specialist will perform the following responsibilities while at each of the contract sites:  supervise aseptic processing operations at the manufacturing facilities.  Review and approve associated batch records and facilitate resolution of production issues.  Train support personnel and ensure that applicable SOPs, batch records, cGMPs and contractual agreements are being followed.  Monitor facility activities and assess impact on equipment and processing operations.  Support process development and validation projects.  Assist with audits, regulatory submissions, and inspection preparedness efforts.  Manage intercompany communication between Genentech and the Contact Manufacturer.  Host periodic review meetings at Genentech and the contract sites.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS in Life Science, with 3-5 years Pharmaceutical Manufacturing experience preferred.  You must be willing to travel approximately 50% of the time.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

