Act as primary Technical Writer and documentation resource for Vacaville Operations.  Potential exists for position to develop into a team leader type role with increasing leadership responsibilities.  Create and revise controlled documents associated with the Facility and Manufacturing operations.  Documents will include Standard Operating Procedures (SOP), Manufacturing Formulae and Forms.  Work closely with Manufacturing, Quality and Validation personnel.  Assist in the restructuring of documentation content and format, based on the principles of Information Mapping.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Prior Technical Writing experience.  Five years experience in pharmaceutical or GMP regulated industry, preferably in Quality or Manufacturing. Working knowledge of MS Word.  Motivated self starter who can work independently.  Ability to organize and prioritize workload.  Ability to deal with aggressive schedules. Knowledge of biochemical manufacturing processes, equipment and facilities.  Bachelor?s degree including relevant coursework in physical or biological sciences.  Flexible team player with excellent communication skills and attention to detail.  Demonstrated leadership ability.     
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
