<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Reporting to the Director of Biochemical Manufacturing, the manager will be responsible for planning, organizing and controlling the activities in the Recovery area of Genentech's large scale recombinant DNA protein production plant in Vacaville. This includes scheduling and control of production activities . Primary responsibility will include supervision of an around the clock operation as well as certain technical aspects of the facilities and processes. Initially the location will be in South San Francisco until the plant is ready for start-up, which is expected to be by mid-to-late 1997. The manager will be a key member or leader of the facility start-up and GMP documentation teams. There will be heavy emphasis on recruitment of technicians and training program design and implementation as well as transfer of processes into the new facility.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS/BA in a science or engineering discipline with significant experience working in a technical or management role within the biotechnology or related industry including at least five years experience in operational supervision in an industrial scale environment. Candidate must have demonstrated the ability to promote a team environment and to successfully supervise people in a highly technical workplace with round-the clock operations. A high level of interpersonal and communication skills is required.  A strong  background in GMP's , FDA regulations , and quality control is required.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
