<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Material Specialist
Requisition #:    96-0000618

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Under the supervision of the Material Operations Supervisor, the Material Specialist is responsible for receipt, verification, record keeping, distribution and shipment of materials and goods.  Responsibilities include: sign for in-coming material; including verification of quantity and condition, preparation of Receiving documents and routing of Receiving information, observation of particular handing, storage or temperature requirements.  Prepare shipping documents, pack shipments, hazardous materials manifesting and placarding.  Perform inventory checks, reconciliation and regular cycle counts.  Maintain equipment, work sites and areas of responsibility in a clean, safe, orderly manner.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Minimum 2 years college and prior material handling/warehousing a plus.  Knowledge of various chemicals and solvents.  Good organizational and interpersonal skills.  Good physical coordination with the ability to lift 50 lbs.  Good mathematical ability.  Experience with forklift, bobtail trucks and material handling equipment desirable.  Capable of performing detailed work with a high degree of accuracy.  Ability to work overtime as required.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
