<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Programmer/Analyst
Requisition #:    97-0000013

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Applies modern information technology tools and techniques to the solution of Genentech's business problems.  Develops, enhances, integrates or supports computer systems, computer modules, data management systems, and/or other components of information technology.  Works in specific functional areas to identify requirements.  Development and implementation of solutions require both knowledge of information technology and expertise in the specific functional area.  Solutions entail designing, testing, debugging, documenting, and/or validating systems.  Implementation of solutions involve development of operating procedures and/or training of users.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
MS in relevant field with 3 years of applicable experience; or a BS in a relevant field with 5 years of applicable experience, or 9 years of applicable experience.  Ability to work as part of a large team and to participate in project teams.  Ability to communicate at various levels, interacting and collaborating productively with both colleagues and users.  Ability to learn quickly and apply skills to projects.  Ability to function independently.  Ability to juggle multiple projects, project requests and appropriately prioritize.  Strong interpersonal skills required along with experience in UNIX and C.  Oracle and Windows NT a plus.  POMS, LIMS, or NovaManage experience preferred.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
