<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Research Assistant
Requisition #:    96-0000868

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
This person will carry out studies to troubleshoot and optimize processes involved in the manufacture of marketed products.  Studies will include both laboratory experiments and the collection and analysis of data and samples from the manufacturing plant to assist in the definition of problems encountered in manufacturing and their solutions.  A degree in chemical engineering is highly desirable, together with the ability to apply engineering fundamentals to problems faced in large and small scale operations.  Familiarity with techniques of protein purification and analysis is essential for this position.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
A demonstrated ability to accurately record and communicate results and maintain laboratory notebook is required.  The ideal candidate for this position will be results-oriented, eager to take on significant responsibilities and motivated to make meaningful contributions to the production process and to our understanding unit operations employed in biotechnology.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
