<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Software Development Manager
Requisition #:    96-0001063

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Lead a software development team for Manufacturing and Quality Information systems.  Work in a cross-functional team environment to implement new application packages (ERP, MES, EDMS), enhance existing packages (LIMS), replace legacy systems, integrate applications and develop user specified systems.  Work closely with the corporate IT staff for certain development efforts.  Work with and ensure technical and quality performance is achieved from multiple vendors, contractors, and consultants.  Provide support to validation effort and participate in the development of the validation strategy for the integrated systems.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
MS in Computer Science or related discipline or equivalent experience.  A minimum of 3-5 years in a development management position preferably in a fast-paced, regulated environment.  Familiarity and/or experience with EDMS, MES, LIMS, and ERP computer systems a plus.  Experience with formal software development and implementation life cycle methods.  Commercial experience with distributed applications in the UNIX environment.  Knowledge of system design concepts, relational database theory and design, client/server systems, TCP/IP network communications and FDA or other regulated industry systems testing and validation methodologies.  Knowledge of UNIX, C, C++, Windows NT, Oracle, Macintosh, and Web technologies preferred.  Demonstrated leadership, verbal and written communication skills.  Strong interpersonal, technical leadership, and project management skills.  Proven track record of product/project delivery.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

