<html> <head>
<title>Job Posting 96-0000921</title>
<!-- This page generated by the /usr/local/etc/httpd/tool-box/../packages/jobpost/production/bin/jobpost_submit script -->
<meta name=gne-generated content=/usr/local/etc/httpd/tool-box/../packages/jobpost/production/bin/jobpost_submit>
</head> <body bgcolor=#ffffff>
<center>
<!-- begin-gne-header -->
<a href=/cgi-bin/imagemap/career>
<img border=0 src=/Career/career.gif alt="Career Sphere" ismap></a>
<!-- end-gne-header -->
</center>
<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Technology Group Sr. Manager/Assoc. Dir./Dir. - Vacaville 
Requisition #:    96-0000921

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Reporting to the General Manager, the leader of the Technology Group will have responsibility for Technical Services, Manufacturing Sciences and Facility/Process Product Engineering functions at Genentech's newly constructed pharmaceutical production plant in Vacaville.   Automation and Control Engineering and Software Support activities may also be part of this group.  Initially, the location will be in South San Francisco until the plant is ready for start-up which is expected to be by mid-to-late 1997.  The job will involve partnering with project engineering, validation, manufacturing, maintenance, quality and process development teams throughout the construction, start-up, validation and regulatory approval phases to ensure the successful transfer of new processes and licensing of the facility.  Ongoing activities may include process, equipment and control system troubleshooting, design and implementation of scale-up and clinical supply batches, and involvement in new large-facility projects for the Vacaville site.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Exceptionally high degree of proven leadership capability in process development and a solid understanding of FDA regulations and protein characteristics.  Strong communication and interpersonal skills.  At least a BS degree in Science or Engineering disciplines and a minimum of 8 years experience in the biotechnology or pharmaceutical industry.  A postgraduate degree is a plus.  Adaptability to changing and demanding workload situations and commitment to building a high quality work group.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
