<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Training Manager
Requisition #:    96-0000797

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
A Training Manager is needed to support an integrated multi-software/hardware systems implementation project in operations area.  Training requirements will include manufacturing/operations best practices (i.e. inventory management, planning, etc.) and training on systems to implement new business practices.  The Training Manager will work with Project Team Leaders and Functional Managers to assess and determine training needs for employees whose job function is impacted by systems implementation.  Create training programs catering to multiple learning styles and multiple levels of experience.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Degree in Industrial Technology or related.  Implementation of business systems in manufacturing environment.  Developing training programs for computer based activities for adults.  Develop training programs for re-engineered environment.  Ability to work in a collaborative team-based environment.  Hands-on training in a GMP and validated environment.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

