Position:         Human Resources Consultant
Requisition #:    96-0000993

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
This person will be responsible for providing strategic human resource consulting supporting the achievement of Genentech's business objectives, goals, and values.  This consulting entails, but is not limited to participation in decision-making, relative to the strategic direction of assigned organizations; provide leadership, human resource advice, consultation and information to respective management team on people-related issues; develop and implement solutions to organizational and people-related problems based upon an on-going knowledge of the environment and an analysis of situation-specific alternatives; ensure that respective human resource planning is consistent with business needs; responsible for the design of new programs or processes that meet business needs of the organization and influence the success of the design and implementation of Human Resource policies, systems and programs.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Must have at least ten years of progressively responsible experience in human resources with exposure to, and demonstrated competence in all functional areas.  Must possess superior written and verbal communication skills, and have proven facilitation skills.  Need the ability to effectively interface with all levels of the organization.  Possess knowledge equivalent to that typically gained in a Bachelor's level degree program.
