<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Manager - Managed Care Strategy
Requisition #:    96-0000950

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The Manager will be actively involved in four major areas of activities and responsibilities: customer/market trend assessment, MC marketing strategy, pricing and contracting strategies, competitive monitoring.  The Manager will develop, identify and/or select primary and secondary market research tools and vendors.  Identify and track major issues identified by our primary MC customer segments.  Work with Field Managed Care to identify topics and advisors.  Work with outside consultants to organize meeting logistics and follow-up.  Survey Field Managed Carepersonnel and findings of market/customer trend analyses to identify program and promotional tactical opportunities.  Coordinate Managed Care Market Planning Input and Output Session (MPIS and MPOS) activities to solicit field input.  Identify and manage field program teams to develop implementation plans for marketing strategies.  Coordinate legal, regulatory, field managed care, marketing and sales administration activities to develop contract implementation plans.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BA/BS required, MS or MBA strongly preferred.  Minimum of two years of managed care experience, preferably in a managed care organization of the managed care division of a major pharmaceutical or biopharmaceutical manufacturer.  Minimum of five years analytical experience.  In-depth understanding of the managed care marketplace and the incentives that motivate all of its players.  Must have word processing, spreadsheet, database management, presentation computer skills.  Demonstrated ability to manage multiple, simultaneous, complex tasks and meet deadlines.  Demonstrated communication, motivational skills and tact to coordinate activities of multiple departments within the company (without direct line authority).  Demonstrated presentation skills in small and large group settings.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
