<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Senior Calibration Tech II
Requisition #:    97-0000034

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
To provide calibration, and repair of instrument, analytical equipment and associated devices.   Organize and maintain measurement standards and test equipment.  Prepare and organize technical documentation and operation procedures.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
AA degree or equivalent in electronic, metrology, or a related major plus substantial on-the-job training.  Minimum of 2 years in instrument calibration or a closely related job.  Must be proficient in calibration techniques of analog and digital electronic, electromechanical, electrochemical, pneumatic, mechanical, thermometric, photometric, and dimensional devices/systems.  General knowledge of metrology, GMP, and GLP.  Practical knowledge of the Life Sciences or chemistry, and familiarity with the operation of analytical instruments.  Must be able to perform work without direct supervision.  Must have good oral and written communication skills.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

