<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Senior Facilities Planner
Requisition #:    96-0001004

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
This position has primary responsibility for coordination and control of space allocation and interiors utilization, as well as interior design standards development for the corporation.  Responsibilities include the identification, generation and implementation of all aspects of space development and utilization.  This person will serve as principal liaison between Genentech and outside planning or architectural firms for pre-planning of assigned capital projects.  Additionally, will provide planning support for other departmental or corporate needs within areas of expertise, as required.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS in Engineering or BA in Architecture; MBA preferred.  Minimum eight years experience required in architecture and facilities management with a minimum of three years spent in a comparable position.  Ideal candidate will have served in a similar role in a corporate planning or design position within the industrial sector.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
