<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Senior Instrument Technician
Requisition #:    97-0000038

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
This is a journeyman-level position with responsibilities which include to provide diagnostics, repairs, and modification of industrial process control instrumentation.  To assist with engineering and evaluation of new instrumentation and process control systems.  Prepare and organize technical documentation and operation procedures.  Provide technical leadership to junior-level technicians.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Completion of an Instrumentation or Industrial Electronic (2-year) curriculum at a technical school, or an AA/AS Degree in a related science or engineering major plus substantial relevant on-the-job training.  At least two years of progressive experience in manufacturing process control instrumentation or closely related jobs with a proven performance record.  Thorough knowledge of the fundamental operating principles of industrial process instrumentation and systems.  Must be proficient in ISA standards and practices for instrumentation .   Thorough knowledge of PID control theories and techniques, relay ladder logic and programmable controllers.  Practical knowledge of computer-aided manufacturing automation.  Ability to read and interpret engineering documents and to produce shop schematics.  Must have good oral and written communication skills.  Must be able to work different shifts with no direct supervision.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
