This person will function as an Executive Assistant to two Corporate Attorneys responsible for a wide range of administrative duties.  Typing, preparation and proofreading of general corporate agreements, pleadings and other documents, general correspondence and various forms and contracts.  Litigation experience and proficiency in Windows Word Perfect on IBM-type computer is essential.  Ability to use discretion in regards to confidential information and able to handle various matters using independent judgment.  Ability to work independently and under deadlines is very important.  This person will answer phones and make follow-up calls, maintain attorneys' calendars, files, scheduling of appointments, conference/meeting arrangements, and make travel arrangements.  Learn and perform routine legal department procedures.  Open, prioritize, and distribute attorneys' mail.
