<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Senior Programmer Analyst
Requisition #:    96-0000102

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Perform systems programming and graphics applications development tasks on UNIX workstations.  Work performed will include:  develop graphics applications in collaboration with other staff in the scientific computing department; perform systems programming tasks as required on SGI and Sun systems in support of the Systems Operations group; act as a general depth resource for SGI and Sun systems; port systems programs form other operating environments to SGI and Sun systems.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS in computer science or related area.  BioScience background considered a plus.  Experience developing graphics applications using GL, OpenGL, and/or Open Inventor.  Demonstrated ability to design, develop, document, and deploy a non-trivial program written C or C++.  Must have expert knowledge of SGI graphics development and of the IRIX operating environment.  General knowledge of the UNIX operating system.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
