<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Accountant
Requisition #:    96-0001054

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Accountant will be responsible for reporting to majority shareholder, which includes financial statements, inter-company account confirmations and development collaboration cost settlements.  Position will also play a key role in reporting to some external agencies.  There will be some monthly general ledger responsibilities.  Interactions include people in other areas of Finance, as well as Corporate Communications and Legal.  The position will play a key role in reviewing selected agreements with third parties and will participate in various special projects.  Position will be responsible for participating in various special projects.  Will be responsible for participating in the implementation of GNE's new financial system, as related to his/her job responsibilities.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS/BA in Business Administration, CPA license, and 3 to 5 years work experience required.  SEC reporting experience required.  Strong written and verbal skills, and the ability to work as part of accounting team and with changing priorities are key.  Knowledge of MS Word and Excel, and ability to learn the majority shareholder reporting software are important.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
