<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Financial Analyst
Requisition #:    96-0000302

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The Marketing and Sales Financial analyst will serve a key role in developing, reporting and analyzing financial information for the Marketing and Sales Organization.  Job responsibilities include the following:  working in close cooperation with Marketing and Sales Management, the Marketing and Sales Group controller and the Funding Coordinator, gather and maintain substantive detail which supports the creation of month-end journal entries and accounting accruals; serve a supporting role in the development of Marketing and Sales budgets and plans; responsible for the accuracy of the budget loads to the general ledger via the BudgetMaker program; assist the Group Controller in developing management reporting for senior Marketing and Sales staff, including tracking reports for headcount, expenses and capital; service as a liaison between Marketing and Sales management and information systems personnel regarding systems based solutions to management information needs, serving on relevant task forces and committees as appropriate; perform a variety of special financial analysis projects as necessary.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS/BA in business administration and three or more years of financial pharmaceutical industry experience or an MBA with relevant financial analysis experience.  Excellent communication skills, attention to detail and customer service orientation.  Proficiency with various financial analysis methodologies.  Exhibited skill in using Macintosh computers and resident software programs, especially Microsoft Excel.  Willingness to exercise considerable flexibility in assignments.  Sales and Marketing experience is desirable.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
