<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Group Controller
Requisition #:    96-0000955

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Develop budgets and financial forecasts for the Medical Affairs group.  Coordinate development of the financial portions for the Medical Affairs long range plan.   Analyze Medical Affairs' operations, assess their financial implications and recommend courses of action.  Work closely with the business managers of each Medical Affairs operating unit to streamline work processes.  Take a prominent role in negotiating contracts with outside vendors.  Review contract to confirm adherence to Medical Affairs financial standards.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
MBA or equivalent experience required; BS in a life science preferred. At least five years experience in the biotechnology/pharmaceutical industry required, preferably in a clinical setting.  The ideal candidate would have work experience as a Clinical Research Associate conducting clinical trials in either a biotechnology/pharmaceutical firm or a Clinical Research Organization, then additional experience in biotech finance.  Must be independent and results oriented with strong interpersonal and communication skills.  Must have a 'hands-on' attitude.   Should be comfortable working in a fast-paced environment with frequent tight deadlines.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
