<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Project Expeditor
Requisition #:    97-0000029

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The Project Expediter will be responsible for expediting of Genetech purchases equipment including g expediting of engineering documentation, material acquisition, fabrication and coordinator of shipping arrangements.  Additionally, the Project Expediter will monitor schedule activities of certain Engineering and Construction Management firms in support of designated Genentech capital projects.  The Project Expediter will act as the functional liaison between the central office purchasing staff and the Project Engineering and Process Engineering Departments for material and equipment expediting.  The Project Expediter will also assist in the formation and administration of various Engineering and construction Management/General Contractor Agreements.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
5+ years experience in expediting or planning and scheduling for a manufacturing, engineering or construction management firm.  Knowledge and experience with engineered mechanical, electrical, control system, and process related equipment.  Computerized expediting and scheduling systems experience.  Experience in the pharmaceutical or biotechnology industry a plus.  BA/BS degree in business or construction management or engineering plus specific training in expediting and/or planning and scheduling. Good oral and written communication abilities. Analytical ability and assertiveness.  Independent judgment and initiative. Ability to work in a fast paced environment on a variety of projects.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
