<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Manager - Market Forecasting
Requisition #:    96-0001038

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The Manager of Market Forecasting in the Marketing Planning group will provide ongoing sales forecasting and long range planning support for Genentech's commercial and development products.  This individual will work with-and improve upon-the company-wide Long Range Planning model, develop vial-based forecast models for in-line products, and interact with professionals in Corporate Finance, Business Development, and Product Development to determine the value potential of Genentech's rich development pipeline.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS in Business, Finance or Computer Science.  Graduate degree (MBA/MS) in Finance, Computer Science or Economic Engineering Systems required.  3-5 years sales and long-range forecasting in a biotechnology, pharmaceutical and/or consulting firm.  Expertise in evaluating, designing and implementing forecasting systems and processes to increase accuracy and improve decision making.  Project management experience in long-range planning, product pricing analysis, sales forecasting, decision analysis, probabilistic simulation, and evaluation of business opportunities.  In-depth knowledge of major forecasting tools, including Excel, I-Think, Crystal Ball, multivariate regressions.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

