<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Manager/Sr. Manager - Marketing Planning
Requisition #:    95-0000636

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The Manager/Senior Manager of Market Planning will provide analytical and ongoing marketing research support for products in development and on-market.  This includes forecasting, conducting marketing research surveys and market planning activities related to a specific therapeutic area, which can be Endocrine, Cardiovascular, and Oncology.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS/BA in Biology, one of the Life Sciences, or Economics.  Either an MBA with a concentration in Marketing or prior product management experience with a strong analytical background.  Must have 3-5 years of project management experience in a pharmaceutical or biotechnology company with revenues of $250m+, or 3-5 years project management experience in a health care supply consulting practice, with projects of &100K for 2-3 months duration.  Demonstrated expertise with broad range of marketing research techniques, including focus group work, product concept testing, conjoint studies, routine share tracking studies, and promotional testing work.  At least 3 years experience in developing and using Excel-based forecasting and valuation tools in a marketing environment.  2-3 years working with industry-specific marketing databases, which include IS, Scott-Levin, HCIA, NCHS.  2-3 years direct experience hiring, managing, and developing Associates/Sr. Associates in analytical positions.  At least 5 years experience in the biopharmaceutical or health care industry.
<p>
<hr><em>
