Position:         Scientist
Requisition #:    96-0001017

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
A Scientist is required to join the Endocrinology and Metabolism group.  The successful candidate will be expected to develop and independent research program investigating the molecular mechanisms that control food intake, fuel homeostasis and adipocyte differentiation and development.  The research program is expected to lead to the development of drugs that will be useful for the treatment of obesity and type II diabetes.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
A Ph.D. and post-doctoral experience in relevant areas of biology and significant experience in molecular and cellular biology.
