<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Supervisor - Quality Assurance
Requisition #:    96-0000957

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Supervise a group of specialists in the Product Release Group in QA who are responsible for final batch assembly/review and product release.  Train, set goals and expectations for the specialists and complete performance evaluations including performance updates; work with specialists to fully develop their potential within job responsibilities.  Work with QA supervisors and managers to facilitate availability of product release information between all groups, as well as with other groups in QC, manufacturing, production planning, materials control, regulatory.  Schedule workloads and determine priorities for batch assembly review and product release to assure market and clinical needs are met.  Assure compliance with product licenses and submissions as these requirements apply to product release.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS/BA in Science or equivalent education/experience.  Minimum 5 years experience working with Quality Assurance systems and/or Manufacturing processes in a cGMP environment.  Prior supervisory experience required.  Good interpersonal and communication skills.  Product batch review and/or product release experience preferred.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
