<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Senior Manager - QC Stability
Requisition #:    97-0000010

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
This Senior Manager will be responsible for the management of all QC Stability testing for Genentech's marketed and clinical products.  The responsibilities of the position include managing the design and testing of stability timepoints according to standard operating procedure protocols, preparing stability reports for submission to regulatory agencies including BLA and MAA applications, reviewing and evaluating stability data, implementing cGMP/compliance regulation, and providing the overall leadership to a QC laboratory group of 20 people.  This position requires interacting with various departments within Genentech to develop and assess specific stability studies.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Ph.D. in Biochemistry or similar discipline, and a minimum of 5 years experience (including management) in the biopharmaceutical/biotechnology industry is required.  A strong working knowledge of protein  chemistry and familiarity with protein HPLC, gel electrophoresis, bioassays and other analytical techniques is essential.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
