<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         QC Analyst
Requisition #:    96-0001035

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
This position involves development, organization and validation of nucleic acid methodologies to be used in a QC environment.  A sound knowledge of molecular biological techniques is required, especially those related to PCR, cloning and sequencing.  The candidate must have proficient laboratory skills and will be required to train other analysts during transfer of new methods to testing groups.  Once the assay has been transferred the candidate will be expected to provide technical support for the testing laboratories.  Participation as team player within the group is essential and being able to interact with individuals outside of the group is expected.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
A BS in molecular biology or related field is required.  A minimum of 1 year laboratory experience, preferably within a pharmaceutical; setting, is recommended.  Familiarity with cGMP compliance is helpful.
<p>
