<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         QA Senior Associate
Requisition #:    97-0000011

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The QA Master Change Control (QAMCC) Senior Associate is responsible for providing quality management for changes which are to be made to validated systems, marketed or clinical processes, raw materials specifications, test procedures, facilities, and any documentation which affects these changes.  For every change, the QAMCC Senior Associate will perform thorough evaluations, determine approvals and testing required, and coordinate the processing and implementation of these changes.  The QAMCC Senior Associate will participate on engineering, manufacturing, and development project teams and will coordinate related change activities for their area of assignment.  The QAMCC Senior Associate will utilize available systems such as ECOs, DCRs, or Novamanage EDMS in order to process and approve changes for the area of assignment.  This position will serve as the Sr. Associate for the Vacaville area after completing of initial training.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS/BA degree in a relevant scientific/technical discipline.  Minimum of  8 years experience in the pharmaceutical industry.  At least 5 years of experience in a GMP operations environment, with working familiarity with major processing equipment, utilities, facilities, PLC software, and basic biotechnology processes so as to be able to make appropriate judgments and evaluations of proposed changes. Working knowledge of federal regulations and guidelines and industry quality standards, specifically with regard to GMP documentation and validation standards.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
