<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         QA Contract Manufacturing Specialist
Requisition #:    97-0000030

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Responsible for handling Quality Assurance on-site coverage of contract manufactured products, minimizing product risk by ensuring that products are manufactured in compliance with Genentech Standard Operating Procedures and cGMPs.  In conjunction with Genentech Contract Manufacturing personnel, interact with management on the contract manufacturer on technical and non-technical issues, problem-solving, and on-going qualifications.   Evaluate and communicate significant campaign events to Genentech or Contract management to ensure immediate resolution.  Responsible for providing technical assistance to the contractor and training as needed.  Coordinate and perform on-site batch record reviews efficiently and in support of product release timelines.  Assist with the development of new contract manufacturing sites to enable successful manufacturing of qualification lots and clinical supplies.  Discuss quality concerns as required to improve systems or procedures.  Effectively communicate corrective actions to minimize or eliminate repetitive contract manufacturing problems.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS/BA or higher in a relevant scientific/technical discipline.  Minimum of 5 years in a GMP environment with strong Manufacturing, Process Development, or Quality experience.  Must possess a strong knowledge of cGMPs for drugs and/or biologics and their applicability to manufacturing activities.  Knowledge of biological and/or pharmaceutical process/product operations, preferably aseptic manufacturing, is essential.  Excellent technical, organizational, communication and interpersonal skills.  Must have high quality standards and possess the ability to assess manufacturing/quality issues soundly in the best interest of Genentech and the customer.  Decisions require judgment which will ensure compliance with Federal/State regulations and/or Genentech quality standards.  Must be self-directed and able to work with minimal to moderate supervision.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

