<html> <head>
<title>Job Posting 97-0000055</title>
<!-- This page generated by the /usr/local/etc/httpd/tool-box/../packages/jobpost/production/bin/jobpost_submit script -->
<meta name=gne-generated content=/usr/local/etc/httpd/tool-box/../packages/jobpost/production/bin/jobpost_submit>
</head> <body bgcolor=#ffffff>
<center>
<!-- begin-gne-header -->
<a href=/cgi-bin/imagemap/career>
<img border=0 src=/Career/career.gif alt="Career Sphere" ismap></a>
<!-- end-gne-header -->
</center>
<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Research Associate
Requisition #:    97-0000055

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The successful candidate will join a process development group working on discovering, optimizing, characterizing and scaling-up of pharmaceutical protein recovery processes from laboratory to production scale.  The work includes employment of numerous protein purification unit operations and exploration of promising new technologies  The successful candidate will be highly motivated and capable of working independently towards achievement of project goals, organized, and interested in sharing intellectual and technical development accomplishments.  The ability to work towards project goals with minimal supervision is a necessity.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS with MS preferred in an appropriate discipline such as Chemistry, Biochemistry, or Chemical Engineering.  Experience with process development or protein purification unit operations is advantageous.  Experience or training in computers and instrumentation is also desirable.  Independence in planning, executing, and summarizing experimental data is essential.
