<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Post-Doctoral Scientist
Requisition #:    96-0000858

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
Will carry out independent research on acute ischemic stroke.  Candidate must have a Ph.D. in physiology-pharmacology or equivalent with a minimum of two years working with models of acute ischemic stroke.  Preferred candidates will have either some experience of molecular biology techniques and/or MRI imaging or at least an interest in learning the requisite technology to carry out work directed at understanding the mechanism of neuronal cell death following focal ischemia.  Areas of interest include the role of neutrophils and oxygen free radicals in reperfusion injury; the effects of thrombolytic therapy and reperfusion on the blood brain barrier and cerebral oedema in the context of acute focal ischemia; the use of neuronal growth factors to affect the course of apoptotic cell death.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>

<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

