<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Post Doc
Requisition #:    96-0000249

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
A postdoctoral research position exists in the protein NMR group.  The main focus of the group is to apply and develop techniques for studying protein structure and dynamics.  In addition the group undertakes studies of biologically active peptides and small molecules with particular emphasis on determining their conformations.  For examples of recent work see:  Fairbrother et al. (1994) Biochemistry 33, 8897-8904; Fairbrother et al. (1994) J. Mol. Biol. 242, 252-270; Skelton et al. (1994) Biochemistry 33,13581-13592; Skelton et al. (1995) Biochemistry 34, 5329-5342.  The NMR facility is part of the Protein Engineering Department and complements protein engineering, protein crystallography and modeling efforts.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Applicants must have experience in biomolecular NMR spectroscopy.  Additional experience with molecular biology and/or protein chemistry is preferred.  Familiarity with protein structure determination using NMR data is also advantageous.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
