<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         Scientist
Requisition #:    95-0000183

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The majority of the individuals time will involve collaborative and independent research supporting the discovery research efforts of the company.  She/He will be expected to work closely with scientists from multiple disciplines to design and conduct experiments to evaluate the efficacy and safety of recombinant proteins and other biotechnological therapeutic approaches in animal model systems.  The individual will support the preclinical safety program supporting regulatory submissions by working with a team of toxicologists and study monitors to design, coordinate and review studies conducted in compliance with GLP regulations.  The primary contribution of the pathologist to this team will be to provide expertise in the area of clinical and anatomical pathology, and to conduct pathology peer reviews as needed. 
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
DVM/VMD and Board Certification in Veterinary Pathology or equivalent.  Advanced research training with a Ph.D. in comparative pathology, postdoctoral experience, and at least 3 years of direct experience in experimental pathology is highly desirable.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

