Requisition #:    96-0000835

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
This individual will develop methods for analysis of protein titer and protein variants in Cell Culture and E coli fermentation samples.  In collaboration with process development researchers, this person will determine the sources and mechanisms of variant production by purification of proteases, isomerases, or other constituents which contribute to unwanted product heterogeneity.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
Experience in protein chemistry, protein purification and state of the art analytical instrumentation are required.  The candidate should have extensive background in chromatography, electorphoresis and protein characterization.  Some background in biological mass spectrometry would be valuable as would experience with E coli or mammalina cell culture.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
