<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         QA Senior Associate
Requisition #:    96-0001022

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The QA Master Change Control (QAMCC) Senior Associate is responsible for providing quality management for changes which are to be made to validated systems, marketed or clinical processes, raw materials specifications, test procedures, facilities, and any documentation which affects these changes.  For every change, the QAMCC Senior Associate will perform thorough evaluations, determine approvals and testing required, and coordinate the processing and implementation of these changes.  The QAMCC Senior Associate will participate in engineering, manufacturing, and development project teams and will coordinate related changedactivities for their Area of Assignment.  The QAMCC Senior Associate will utilize the Novamanage Electronic Document Management System (EDMS) to implement changes for the Area of Assignment.  This particular position will serve as the Sr. Associate for the CCP area upon implementation of the 1st wave of SYNOPSIS.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
BS/BA in a relevant scientific/technical discipline.  Minimum 8 years experience in the pharmaceutical industry.  At least 5 years of experience in a GMP operations environment, with working familiarity with major processing equipment, utilities, facilities, PLC software, and basic biotechnology processes so as to be able to make appropriate judgments and evaluations of proposed changes.  Working knowledge of federal regulations and guidelines and industry quality standards, specifically with regard to GMP documentation and validation standards.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

