Position:         Scientist
Requisition #:    96-0000974

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The Medicinal & Analytical Chemistry Department has a position open at the Scientist level to conduct research and development for the characterization of recombinant DNA-derived polypeptides, proteins, and glycoproteins.  The position involves a significant amount of problem-solving related to product characterization using electrophoretic, chromatographic, and mass spectral techniques.  Experience in the use of capillary electrophoretic methods including capillary isoelectric focusing and non-gel sieving is preferred.  Good communication skills are essential along with the ability to conduct independent research.
