<blockquote>
<center><h1>Genentech, Inc.</h1></center>
<center><h3>Job Posting</h3></center>
<hr>
<pre>
Position:         QC Lead Analyst
Requisition #:    97-0000056

</pre>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Description</strong><br>
The QC Lead Analyst will be responsible for coordination of testing and activities that occur on Wednesday through Saturday graveshift.  In addition, the lead is responsible for technical review of analytical data and training of analysts on the shift.  The successful candidate will also perform a variety of biochemical analysis on Genentech marketed and clinical products.  These assays will be performed in compliance with cGMPs and support in-process and cleaning changeover testing.  Methods that will be utilized include: endotoxin determinations by the LAL method, UV spectroscopy, SDS-PAGE, ELISA, HPLC and a variety of assays utilizing wet chemistry techniques.  The QC Lead will contribute to the organization and maintenance of general lab systems to assure cGMP compliance, regulatory audit readiness, and efficiency of the QCMP labs during the graveshift.
<p>
<p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong><br>
A BS/BA in Biochemistry, Chemistry or related scientific field.  Strong analytical and technical skills.  HPLC and/or ELISA experience desirable.  Effective communication as well as good organizational and leadership skills are required.  The successful candidate is self-motivated, reliable, and able to work independently.  Need  strong attention to detail, and a demonstrated ability to adapt tochanging priorities.  Able to work effectively as part of the graveshift and in-process testing team.
<p>
<hr><em>
Send resume to <a href=mailto:jobs@gene.com>jobs@gene.com</a></em>

</blockquote>
