<title>Physics Resources - Papers</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>
<img src="/images/atom.xbm">
Physics Internet Resources - Papers
</h1>
<hr>

<h2>Physics Papers</h2>


<ul>
<li> <a href="papers.html">A primer on electronic reading
and writing</a>
<p>

<li> <b>Preprints</b>
<p>

<dl>

<dt> <a href="http://xxx.lanl.gov/">
     Los Alamos Physics Information Service </a>
<dd> Main archive for physics preprint source files and the
     site to which you can submit your papers.
     The standard TeX macro packages are available here.
     Services are also available via FTP and e-mail:
     for introductory info send an e-mail message with 
     "Subject: help" to hep-th@xxx.lanl.gov.

<dt> <a href="/htbin/preprints.html">
     Brown Physics Preprint Gateway </a>
<dd> An alternate jumping-off point for preprints.

<dt> <a href="http://www.cern.ch/Physics/LANL.html">
     Other preprint gopher servers</a>
<dd> Pointers to servers in areas not at LANL

<dt> <a href="http://www-spires.slac.stanford.edu/find/hep">
     SPIRES HEP bibliography search</a>
<dd> The database at SLAC contains papers from the last 20 years.
     It can be searched by author, title, date, citation, etc.
     If you want to know where that preprint you've been working with
     was published, look here.
     The search results now include hyperlinks directly to papers
     on the bulletin boards.

</dl>
<p>
<li> <b>Journals</b>
<p> The traditional journals are rapidly adapting to electronic
     communication.  Many journals accept submissions by e-mail,
     handle refereeing by e-mail, and typeset from the author's
     TeX.  It's a good idea to look at a recent issue 
     to check on instructions and contacts.  Here is some information
     already on-line:

<dl>
<dt> <i>Physical Review</i> -
<dd> Submission of manuscripts available to pra@aps.org, prb@aps.org, etc.
     Electronic typsetting available for RevTeX format manuscripts.
     There is detailed information from the APS on
     <a href="http://aps.org/PRL/prlinfo.html">
     <i> Physical Review Letters </i>
     </a>
<p>

<dt> <a href="http://www.nucphys.nl/www/pub/nucphys/npe.html">
     <i>Nuclear Physics </i> </a>
<dd> Currently there is a crude "experimental" WWW server with 
     indexes, abstracts, searches, publication status and preprints.
     Some of this is only available for subscribers:  you must register
     with your library's subscription number and the IP number of
     your computers.
<p>
     TeX submissions to <i> Nuclear Physics B</i> 
     can be sent by e-mail to npb@jnl.nucphys.nl.
<p>

<dt> <i>Physics Letters</i>
<dd> See recent issues for info.  Appropriate submissions to
     <i>Physics Letters B</i> can be sent to georgi@huhepl.harvard.edu.


</dl>

</ul>

<hr>
Send additions to
<i>
<a href="/people/mende/index.html"> 
mende@het.brown.edu 
</a>
</i>

</body>
</html>
</DOC>
