<title> Why physics funding is in trouble...</title>
<h1>Why physics funding is in trouble...</h1>


<hr>
From <i>The Boston Globe</i> (April 27, 1994):

<blockquote>

...the huge machine produced a trillion collisions in a year.
Of those, 12 produced signs suggestive of the elusive top quark.
<p>

"If events were dollars," said 
[a spokesman for the lab], 
"that's like taking the entire federal budget and ending up with
12 bucks."

</blockquote>

<hr>
<i>mende@het.brown.edu</i>
