<title> Home page set-up </title>
<h1> Home page set-up </h1>

You can set up or modify a simple home page easily.

<pre>
It is a file that could look like the sample below.
For more information on hypertext documents, 
see <a href="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/General/Internet/WWW/HTMLPrimer.html">A Beginner's Guide to HTML</a>.
To have your home page linked to the <a href="/people/index.html">directory list,</a>
make the file ``www/index.html'' and then send a request 
to webmaster@het.brown.edu.
</pre>

<h2> Sample file: www/index.html </h2>
<PRE>
  &lt;TITLE> Albert Einstein &lt;/TITLE>

  &lt;H1> Albert Einstein &lt;/H1>


  &lt;IMG SRC="sample-albert.gif">


  &lt;H2> Research Interests &lt;/H2>

  Brownian motion, relativity, quantum theory.

  &lt;H2> Papers &lt;/H2>
 
  &lt;UL>

  &lt;LI>  &lt;a href="http://mentor.lanl.gov:80/all.indx?einstein+and+albert">
  Bulletin Board Papers&lt;/a>

  &lt;LI>  Another one

  &lt;/UL>
  &lt;P>


  &lt;H2> Other information &lt;/H2>

  This is one paragraph.&lt;P>

  And this is a second.&lt;P>

  __________________________________________________________________
  &lt;address> einstein@het.brown.edu &lt;/address>



The result looks like this:

</PRE>




  <H1> Albert Einstein </H1>


  <IMG SRC="sample-albert.gif">


  <H2> Research Interests </H2>

  Brownian motion, relativity, quantum theory.

  <H2> Papers </H2>
 
  <UL>

  <LI>  <a href="http://mentor.lanl.gov:80/all.indx?einstein+and+albert">
  Bulletin Board Papers</a>

  <LI>  Another one

  </UL>
  <P>


  <H2> Other information </H2>

  This is one paragraph.<P>

  And this is a second.<P>

  __________________________________________________________________
  <address> einstein@het.brown.edu </address>


</PRE>
