<TITLE>Automatic TeX</TITLE>

<H2>
Automatic TeX
</H2>

When you have the TeX source file in this viewing window, select the
default <B>Print</B> option from the Mosaic <B>File</B> menu
(top left)
to call a script which will run TeX automatically, then preview it.
(Sorry, Mosaic won't let the buttons be re-labeled to something
more descriptive.)
The paper will be stored in the local on-line library
(as a compressed  <I>.dvi</I> file)
for faster browsing and/or printing by other users.
If you are using a guest account, the <I>.dvi</I> files
will be placed in the directory /het/eprints/tmp.


<H2>
Printing
</H2>

To print a paper after previewing it, either use the "Print" option
from the On-Line Library or else select Mosaic's  <B>Print</B> option
a second time and put the command ``<B>texprint</B>'' into the popup window.
Our printing resources are extremely limited, so the file will be locked
after it has been printed once.
Please make a photocopy and leave the original in the box on 5 North
outside the library.



