<title></title>
<pre>
Date:    Wed, 20 Oct 93 15:30:33 PDT
From: barnett@Csa3.LBL.Gov (MICHAEL BARNETT (510)486-5650)
Subject: SSC news
</pre>

  A Member of Congress who is on the Energy and Water conference committee 
is today saying that he will push for the following conference report
(and he hints that Sen. Johnston is considering something similar):
<p>

 ---- This is one Member's idea, NOT the committee's idea ----
<ul>
<li> Mothball SSC for 1-2 years.  Definition of "mothball" is not
        known, but speculation is that it may mean protecting the
        civil construction so that the project could be restarted 
        at a later time.

<li> $10 million for SSC manpower, presumably to protect some SSC
       personnel.

<li> $44 million to be added to the current HEP budget.

<li> $25 million extra for the Fermilab Main Injector.
</ul
<p>

<p>

   It may be assumed that under this scenario the two detector
collaborations (SDC and GEM) would disband.  If the project
was restarted some years later, new collaborations would be formed.
<p>

   I have heard reports that the committee will meet Thursday (Oct. 21),
but also other reports that it will not meet until next week.
<p>

<p>
                               Michael
<p>

